COMMITMENT IS A CHOICE.
CHANGE IS A CHOICE.
GETTING UP EARLY IS A CHOICE.
TAKING RISKS IS A CHOICE.
BLAMING IS A CHOICE.
WAITING IS A CHOICE.
CHOOSING WHAT WAY TO GO IS A CHOICE.
.
CHOICE is one of the most powerful tools we have. Everythign boils down to choice,yes youll get thrown some shitty times and hard challenges but we get to choose what we do with them,how we move on,the meaning we put on them,who we blame,what step is next and how we respond! .
We excist in a world of possibilities,every choice we make , shuts down some doors and opens up new ones.
.
At any point we can change the direction of our lives from who we are around to what we decide to do next. .
Its all in our hands, our hearts and our minds.
.
PLEASE REMEMBER – Most of your stress comes from the way you respond , not the way life is. Adjust your attitude and itll take away all the extra added stress you and your mind/body don’t need.
.
YOU ALWAYS HAVE A CHOICE. What do you choose NEXT?

Now have a think .... 🤔 REMEMBER WHEN YOU WANTED WHAT YOU CURRENTLY HAVE? Or have you forgotten to be in the moment and appreciate it or give yourself a hi 5? .
If you are constantly in forward motion, how often do you stop to look at where you are, what you have and how you live? Having future goals is a MUST don’t get me wrong BUT sometimes stopping and being in the moment of NOW and feeling proud is important.

This picture is from a few weeks ago with extremely good lighting and today I don’t look like this haha to be REALLY honest Today I have honestly felt SO exhausted and shit! .
HORRIBLE sleep last night ( I explained on my snapchat ) and just some general life stress that comes with owning your own business, recovering from surgery,being busy 24/7 and trying to juggle mumlife,supporting those around you,supporting yourself, kicking goals, meeting deadlines, solving problems, health, fitness, friends , family, growth and the list goes on. ANYONE FEEL ME?
.
BUT - I am REAAAAAAAAAAAAALLLLYYY feel proud of how I deal with it all these days,I feel ive grown so much and don’t let myself get my knickers in a twist haha wow that’s something mum use to say to me,in other words don’t allow myself to get super worked up to the point of on the floor anxiety attacks and days of meltdowns and not being able to get out of bed – YEP that use to be me and me trying to deal with LIFE.
.
Ive learned to breathe,yep sounds simple but wow really makes a difference ,Ive also learned that tough times don’t last tough people do,ive learned to accept that life isn’t meant to be easy and no one has it easy and when you accept that, take care of what you can control and let go of what you CANT control you just use your energy where its going to actually help you instead of wasting it on stressed energy.
.
Ive also learned to allow myself to have cry- yes that happened for a moment today now its passed 😉 ,ask for help and lean on those around me when I need some extra support myself.
.
If you are having one of those days I hope you reading this can give you some guidance and tools to help you get through a rough day/week. We can only do so much and we are in control of how we handel each situation. Just do the best you can. ❤ .
Bring on bora bora next month ahhhhh island dreaming 🌴☀️oh and special thanks to those around me who have been my back bone this week you know who you are 😘 Don’t forget to check in on those around you never know when you will make their day brighter 🌟
.

I watched a friend of mine get slammed on Social Media not long ago for sharing her ‘normal’.
We all have body issues. We all have elements of ourselves that we don’t love, and no one has any right whatsoever to tell someone how they should feel about their own body. We forget we all have insecurities and all battle through things that some of you won’t ever know about and forget you only see such small snippets of peoples lives and most of the time the highlights. .
If someone is upset, we have no right to tell them that they shouldn’t be.
If someone is hurt, we have no place to tell them they are over reacting.
If someone is sharing a truth for them, we have zero right to slam them for that because it is after all, their truth. .
It may not be your truth, you may not understand it, you may not “ agree “ but it’s not your place to judge someone else on how they feel. .
Lets all try to be a little bit more tolerant and compassionate towards others in real life and those we come across on Social Media.
If you don’t agree with something, unfollow or just keep scrolling. It really can be that simple or just think twice before commenting and always try to think how you’d feel if someone said it to you, or your best friend or your mum or daughter or sister? How would that make you feel? .

Was randomly thinking today - and decided to make this list to share - 5 THINGS I WISH I NEVER BOTHERED WORRYING ABOUT EVVVVER!!!
. * Whether ‘he’ ‘ she ‘ liked me or not. It doesn’t matter if they like you, what matters is that you like who you are💕 We spend way to many hours hoping to be accepted, when what we really need is to accept ourselves.
.
* A thigh gap 🙄Honestly this is one of the most ridiculous ‘trends’ to ever come about - I’ve even had girls ask why I don’t have one because I should when I’m a “ fitspo “ . For some it’s a natural thing based on the width of their hips, for others it’s physically impossible based on the exact same reason 🤷🏼‍♀️
.
* How ‘it’ would turn out - Even if it doesn’t make sense at the time, I know that given the opportunity we can always find purpose in everything and it works out the exact way it’s meant to. .
* What people say about me - Peoples opinions of us say nothing about us, and everything about them and a lot of the time a reflection of what they are feeling about themselves and just how they choose to spend their time🙅🏼‍♀️
.
* Body Changes - We are always evolving, facing challenges, creating a life and moving through time. We are not meant to look the same as we did five years ago. You aren’t meant to have a pre-baby body after you’ve had a baby. You aren’t meant to look like you’re 18 when you’re 30. Our bodies change and grow as we go through life, our job is to celebrate , appreciate and care for them while we are lucky enough to have them.
.
Turning 30 on Sunday - and I’m really proud of where I am - I feel 30, I feel great, happy, proud, content and healthy 🙌🏽
.
